comments.body:
I think this (`type_argument_not_matching_bounds: ignore`) may drop some potentially useful feedback on the floor (not just strong-mode provoked).  For example, looking at our test cases for this error code, I think it would suppress a warning on the following snippet:

```
class A {}
class B {}
class G<E extends A> {
  const G();
}
f() { return const G<B>(); } //<= should flag B
```

See here: https://dartpad.dartlang.org/fe9b7876ca94a9740916

cc @bwilkerson for more thoughts

If there aren't a lot of these errors it may be safer to ignore them specifically in the source?
